What about governance of deployment models?

00:44:10.439 --> 00:44:12.439
Strategies for cleaning up trash?

00:44:12.439 --> 00:44:15.439
This is a great question.

00:44:15.439 --> 00:44:20.439
So I think a lot of this depends on what infrastructure you're running on.

00:44:20.439 --> 00:44:23.439
I would say, if I'm running it locally,

00:44:23.439 --> 00:44:28.439
I just have to control-C, and it ends the model.

00:44:28.439 --> 00:44:33.439
It might look different for different cloud networks or cloud providers,

00:44:33.439 --> 00:44:37.439
and it'll probably look different if you're on-prem or in a public cloud.

00:44:37.439 --> 00:44:40.439
