But I think if you're not versioning,

00:48:20.439 --> 00:48:23.439
these pitfalls are much deeper.

00:48:23.439 --> 00:48:25.439
You're going to get into a mess of you don't know

00:48:25.439 --> 00:48:26.439
where files are,

00:48:26.439 --> 00:48:29.439
you don't know what you're loading into your environment.

00:48:29.439 --> 00:48:32.439
Without extra cognitive load,

00:48:32.439 --> 00:48:35.439
that could be reduced by versioning.

00:48:35.439 --> 00:48:36.439
Great.

00:48:36.439 --> 00:48:37.439
And for your last question,

00:48:37.439 --> 00:48:41.439
would you like to choose from the list here?

00:48:41.439 --> 00:48:42.439
Sure.

00:48:42.439 --> 00:48:45.439
What are the future plans of vetiver?

00:48:45.439 --> 00:48:51.439
So we have great groundwork laid for this package right now,

00:48:51.439 --> 00:48:53.439
but what we're really interested in doing

00:48:53.439 --> 00:48:57.439
is kind of bolstering the open source side of things.

00:48:57.439 --> 00:49:00.439
We have a one-liner for our pro products,

00:49:00.439 --> 00:49:02.439
which are RStudio Connect as well as some others,

00:49:02.439 --> 00:49:04.439
but it mostly works with Connect.

00:49:04.439 --> 00:49:08.439
But we want to make sure that it's not catered exclusively

00:49:08.439 --> 00:49:12.439
to this persona of people who are paying for our products.

00:49:12.439 --> 00:49:14.439
Open source is a vast field.

00:49:14.439 --> 00:49:18.439
So we want to make sure that we have very good documentation

00:49:18.439 --> 00:49:21.439
for multiple cloud platforms.

00:49:21.439 --> 00:49:27.439
We're starting on the R side with AWS SageMaker and AWS Lambda.

00:49:27.439 --> 00:49:33.439
The Python side is AWS SageMaker is also on our radar,

00:49:33.439 --> 00:49:38.439
as well as some of the Vertex AI, I think, is from GCP.

00:49:38.439 --> 00:49:40.439
That was a lot of just name-dropping.

00:49:40.439 --> 00:49:43.439
In general, it's supporting more robust cloud workflows

00:49:43.439 --> 00:49:45.439
and documenting what that looks like,

00:49:45.439 --> 00:49:47.439
and then also looking at things like

00:49:47.439 --> 00:49:50.439
how can we build up our monitoring section,

00:49:50.439 --> 00:49:52.439
and also, apparently now,

00:49:52.439 --> 00:49:56.439
looking at Spark ML Web Models and A-P testing.

00:49:56.439 --> 00:49:58.439
Thank you so much, Isabel.

00:49:58.439 --> 00:50:00.439
Big hand for our first speaker.

00:50:00.439 --> 00:50:03.439
APPLAUSE

